## General Notes

| Term | Explanation |
|---|---|
| MOSS | 21" tube-launched decoy mimicking submarine acoustic signature to seduce enemy torpedoes |
| ADC | Small ejector-launched noisemaker, shorter range, faster to deploy than MOSS |
| CAPTOR | Seabed-laid mine that releases an encapsulated Mk 46 torpedo on detecting a submarine |
| SLMM | Torpedo-shaped mine that self-propels to a preset location then sinks and arms |
| XBT | Measures ocean temperature gradient to help sonar operators predict detection performance |
| Harpoon (sub-launched) | Encapsulated in torpedo-shaped canister; capsule breaks away as missile surfaces and ignites |
| VLS | Vertical Launch System — fixed tubes forward of the sail, dedicated to Tomahawk, no reloads at sea |

